Data Dictionary — Orders & Sales Dashboard
This data dictionary documents all fields used in the Power BI dashboard, including definitions, data types, and usage notes.

 1. Orders Table
Field Name	Data Type	Description
Order ID	Integer	Unique identifier for each order.
Order Date	Date	Date the order was placed. Used for monthly and yearly trend analysis.
Year	Integer	Extracted from Order Date for time intelligence.
Month	Text	Month name extracted from Order Date.
Total Sales	Decimal	Total revenue generated from the order.
Entrée Description	Text	Text description of the entrée ordered; used for ingredient and cuisine analysis.
2. Restaurant Table
Field Name	Data Type	Description
Restaurant Name	Text	Name of the restaurant fulfilling the order.
City	Text	City where the restaurant is located.
State	Text	State where the restaurant is located; used for geographic analysis.
Restaurant Count	Integer	Distinct count of restaurants in the dataset.
 3. Aggregated Metrics (Calculated Fields)
Metric	Type	Description
Total Sales (KPI)	Measure	SUM of Total Sales across all orders.
Total Orders	Measure	COUNT of Order ID.
Average Sale per Order	Measure	Total Sales ÷ Total Orders.
Orders by City	Measure	COUNT of orders grouped by city.
Sales by State	Measure	SUM of Total Sales grouped by state.
 4. Slicer Fields
Field	Description
Month	Filters visuals by month.
State	Filters visuals by state.
Restaurant Name	Filters visuals by restaurant.
Order Date Range	Allows date‑range filtering.
 5. Supporting Fields
Field	Description
Cuisine Type (optional)	Derived from entrée descriptions (e.g., Mexican, Fast Food).
Ingredient Tags (optional)	Extracted keywords from entrée descriptions.
Order Value Category	Buckets such as Low (<$50), Medium ($50–$150), High (>$150).
